title: White House blames Democrats' 'deliberate and hostile resistance' after Alex Pretti's death in Minnesota
subhed: The administration is scrambling as videos of the latest shooting went viral. Minneapolis Mayor Jacob Frey said 'some federal agents' will begin leaving the city on Tuesday, without providing specifics.

From Tel Aviv to the occupied West Bank, a highway of denial
subhed: Highway 1 cuts across Israel from west to east, from the Mediterranean Sea to the edge of the Dead Sea, and then into the West Bank. Used by Israeli workers and vacationers alike, the strategic route plays a role in invisibilizing any Palestinian presence.

title: The burial of Mohammad Mozafari: A rare look into the Iranian regime's crackdown
subhed: Mohammad Mozafari, 39, was killed on Friday by the Iranian regime. The photos of his burial, obtained by Le Monde, are a rare visual record of the repression carried out behind closed doors.

title: Eiffel Tower to honor 72 women scientists for posterity
subhed: On Monday, a multidisciplinary commission presented the mayor of Paris with a list of 72 names of women who will join the exclusively male scientists whose names are inscribed on the frieze of the 'Iron Lady.'

title: Richard Ford: 'I tell my European friends how it feels not to understand my country'
subhed: The novelist expresses concern, in an op-ed for Le Monde, about the direction his country has taken under President Donald Trump. He laments that Americans do not appear to pay attention to the erosion of their constitutional rights, nor do they grasp how difficult it will be to turn back.

title: France is considering banning phones in high schools. This school near Paris already does.
subhed: The Lycée Michelet, a large school complex with 2,300 students, banned mobile phones in its hallways in April 2025. School officials report positive results from a decision made in agreement with the entire educational community.

title: Generative AI, psychiatry and the risks of self-service therapy
subhed: Millions of people use chatbots like ChatGPT to share their distress, and the scientific community has warned about the risks vulnerable people face. Generative AI has shaken up psychiatric consultations, fueled tech giants' ambitions and emerged as a credible tool for analyzing pathologies.
